verbs.description: demigrate (third-person singular simple present demigrates, present participle demigrating, simple past and past participle demigrated)
demigrate (third-person singular simple present demigrates, present participle demigrating, simple past and past participle demigrated)

entries.meaning: To cancel or return from migration (of e.g. a computer system).
examples: The reason is that it is more cost effective to debug and troubleshoot the new environment than to demigrate and lose all the data transactions completed under the new technology.
